[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Root Cause (observed, not repaired)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m When a `MultiPart` is constructed in-process (as a client would build it),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m each `BodyPart` stores the raw Java object passed to its constructor as its
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m entity.  Here that object is `byte[]`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m On the server side, Jersey's `MultiPartReader` (`MessageBodyReader<MultiPart>`)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m deserialises the HTTP wire bytes and wraps each part's content in a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m `BodyPartEntity` that exposes an `InputStream`.  That HTTP round-trip never
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m happens in a plain unit test, so:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. `(BodyPartEntity) bodyPart.getEntity()` → `ClassCastException: [B cannot be
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    cast to BodyPartEntity` — the entity is still `byte[]`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 2. `bodyPart.getEntityAs(BodyPartEntity.class)` → `IllegalStateException:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    Entity instance does not contain the unconverted content` — `getEntityAs`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    requires the entity to be stored as raw bytes (the "unconverted" wire form),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    which is only the case after the `MessageBodyReader` has parsed the stream.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Assumptions and Caveats
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The original question used Jersey 1.x (`com.sun.jersey`).  Version 1.19.4
